verbose_text: Their plasma very low density lipoprotein and low density lipoprotein (VLDL+ LDL) cholesterol levels are similar on a basal diet, but the levels are markedly different on cholesterol enriched diets because plasma VLDL+ LDL cholesterol is highly elevated (> 10-fold) in high responding opossums, whereas plasma VLDL+ LDL cholesterol is only slightly elevated (< 2-fold) in low responding opossums [XREF_BIBR].
